{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rWushNSfy3iMGV6KFS85w","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n2\t\n3\tReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\n4\tTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `14a4612`.\n5\tBaseline: `277fa4c`.\n6\tCherry-pick: `340502e` on `main`.\n7\tReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-review-20260527T132959Z.log`.\n8\t\n9\tSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly (read-only sandbox). Main thread promoted from the log.\n10\t\n11\t## Verdict: BLOCK\n12\t\n13\t### 1. [high] `doc` as a 7th `source_type` value breaks the HITL lock\n14\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:105`; `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:350`\n15\t\n16\tThe memo explicitly expands the locked vocabulary from 6 values to 7 by admitting `\"doc\"`. HITL says Pack 1 \"MUST use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key,\" and the locked vocabulary immediately above it is `email/article/paper/meeting/note/todo`; there is no approval here to add a synthetic 7th value. Because D3 changes a HITL-locked contract instead of implementing it, this is a blocking design violation. If `doc` must remain in tests, it needs a separate HITL/ADR update or the fixture kind needs to be remapped without changing the locked vocabulary.\n17\t\n18\t### 2. [high] Migration plan relies on vec0 rename support not in the pinned sqlite-vec version\n19\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:183`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1207`; SQLite virtual-table rule (www.sqlite.org/vtab.html); sqlite-vec releases (github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/releases)\n20\t\n21\tThe memo's rebuild shape is `CREATE ... vector_default_v2` → copy rows → `DROP TABLE vector_default` → `ALTER TABLE vector_default_v2 RENAME TO vector_default`. SQLite allows neither `ADD COLUMN` on virtual tables nor arbitrary rename unless the module implements it; sqlite-vec's release notes show `ALTER TABLE RENAME support` appearing in `v0.1.10-alpha.2` (April 2026), while this repo is pinned to `=0.1.7`. The proposed migration is not validated for the version in use. The same section invents an `operational_mutations` schema stamp, but the engine's real migration framework is `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` + `PRAGMA user_version` — gating story mismatched.\n22\t\n23\t### 3. [medium] D6 secondary \"normalized\" fixture is internally incorrect\n24\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:303`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:322`\n25\t\n26\tFirst RED fixture is fine. But the memo claims `normalize([1,-1,1,-1,...])` quantizes identically to the half/half vector because they have \"identical sign patterns at every coordinate.\" They do not: one is half-positive/half-negative, the other alternates signs. Remove or rewrite the secondary assertion.\n27\t\n28\t## What passed on inspection\n29\t\n30\t- D1 supportable: the binary-quant guide shows mixed `float[768]` + `bit[768]` columns in one `vec0` table and `vec_quantize_binary(...)` inside `INSERT ... VALUES`. No evidence the capability is `>=0.1.9` only.\n31\t- D2 capacity math fine: 2 metadata + 1 partition_key, well within vec0 limits (16 / 4).\n32\t- D7 correct: second writer site at `lib.rs:1806`, vector_default insert at `:1838`.\n33\t- D8 reader no-op claim reasonable: reader still queries `embedding MATCH vec_f32(?1)`; metadata/partition columns don't change KNN semantics on the original column.\n34\t\n35\t## Reviewer process notes\n36\t\n37\t- Could not read `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN.md` (absent from this worktree — cut from baseline `277fa4c`, which does not contain the prompt commit landed on main as part of S0 closure).\n38\t- External docs consulted: sqlite-vec binary quant guide, vec0 features doc, metadata release blog, SQLite vtab rules, sqlite-vec release history.\n39\t\n40\t## Orchestrator triage\n41\t\n42\tDate: 2026-05-27.\n43\t\n44\tBLOCK verdict; orchestration.md §10 — never override BLOCK. Fix-1 remediation required.\n45\t\n46\t- **Finding 1 (high)**: Remap. Honor the 6-value HITL lock. Pack 1 must not extend the vocabulary. Decision options for fix-1: (a) map `kind=\"doc\"` to one of the 6 in the writer-side mapping table (e.g., `\"article\"` as the most generic), with no fixture change; (b) change the AC-013 fixture to seed with a locked kind. Recommend (a) — keep fixture changes minimal until the corpus-build work lands, which will exercise all 6 source_types properly.\n47\t- **Finding 2 (high)**: Rewrite D4. Since `vector_default` is fully derivable from canonical state (`_fathomdb_vector_rows` + canonical_nodes), use the existing `rebuild_shadow_state` / `RebuildKind` path: drop the old vec0 virtual table, recreate with the new schema, repopulate via the writer rebuild driver. Schema versioning belongs in `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` + `PRAGMA user_version`, not `operational_mutations`. The memo must cite the actual migration framework anchors.\n48\t- **Finding 3 (medium)**: Remove or rewrite the secondary sign-pattern fixture in D6. The first fixture is sufficient on its own.\n49\t\n50\tFix-1 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-1.md`. Respawn implementer on the existing worktree `/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z`, existing branch.\n51\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15e9754f-2583-43b5-b988-10adeffaf9c5","uuid":"6d4159a6-cc5b-4515-80ac-2f044f13ff42","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:36:08.605Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-review-20260527T132959Z.md","content":"# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n\nReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\nTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `14a4612`.\nBaseline: `277fa4c`.\nCherry-pick: `340502e` on `main`.\nReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-review-20260527T132959Z.log`.\n\nSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly (read-only sandbox). Main thread promoted from the log.\n\n## Verdict: BLOCK\n\n### 1. [high] `doc` as a 7th `source_type` value breaks the HITL lock\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:105`; `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:350`\n\nThe memo explicitly expands the locked vocabulary from 6 values to 7 by admitting `\"doc\"`. HITL says Pack 1 \"MUST use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key,\" and the locked vocabulary immediately above it is `email/article/paper/meeting/note/todo`; there is no approval here to add a synthetic 7th value. Because D3 changes a HITL-locked contract instead of implementing it, this is a blocking design violation. If `doc` must remain in tests, it needs a separate HITL/ADR update or the fixture kind needs to be remapped without changing the locked vocabulary.\n\n### 2. [high] Migration plan relies on vec0 rename support not in the pinned sqlite-vec version\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:183`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1207`; SQLite virtual-table rule (www.sqlite.org/vtab.html); sqlite-vec releases (github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/releases)\n\nThe memo's rebuild shape is `CREATE ... vector_default_v2` → copy rows → `DROP TABLE vector_default` → `ALTER TABLE vector_default_v2 RENAME TO vector_default`. SQLite allows neither `ADD COLUMN` on virtual tables nor arbitrary rename unless the module implements it; sqlite-vec's release notes show `ALTER TABLE RENAME support` appearing in `v0.1.10-alpha.2` (April 2026), while this repo is pinned to `=0.1.7`. The proposed migration is not validated for the version in use. The same section invents an `operational_mutations` schema stamp, but the engine's real migration framework is `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` + `PRAGMA user_version` — gating story mismatched.\n\n### 3. [medium] D6 secondary \"normalized\" fixture is internally incorrect\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:303`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:322`\n\nFirst RED fixture is fine. But the memo claims `normalize([1,-1,1,-1,...])` quantizes identically to the half/half vector because they have \"identical sign patterns at every coordinate.\" They do not: one is half-positive/half-negative, the other alternates signs. Remove or rewrite the secondary assertion.\n\n## What passed on inspection\n\n- D1 supportable: the binary-quant guide shows mixed `float[768]` + `bit[768]` columns in one `vec0` table and `vec_quantize_binary(...)` inside `INSERT ... VALUES`. No evidence the capability is `>=0.1.9` only.\n- D2 capacity math fine: 2 metadata + 1 partition_key, well within vec0 limits (16 / 4).\n- D7 correct: second writer site at `lib.rs:1806`, vector_default insert at `:1838`.\n- D8 reader no-op claim reasonable: reader still queries `embedding MATCH vec_f32(?1)`; metadata/partition columns don't change KNN semantics on the original column.\n\n## Reviewer process notes\n\n- Could not read `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN.md` (absent from this worktree — cut from baseline `277fa4c`, which does not contain the prompt commit landed on main as part of S0 closure).\n- External docs consulted: sqlite-vec binary quant guide, vec0 features doc, metadata release blog, SQLite vtab rules, sqlite-vec release history.\n\n## Orchestrator triage\n\nDate: 2026-05-27.\n\nBLOCK verdict; orchestration.md §10 — never override BLOCK. Fix-1 remediation required.\n\n- **Finding 1 (high)**: Remap. Honor the 6-value HITL lock. Pack 1 must not extend the vocabulary. Decision options for fix-1: (a) map `kind=\"doc\"` to one of the 6 in the writer-side mapping table (e.g., `\"article\"` as the most generic), with no fixture change; (b) change the AC-013 fixture to seed with a locked kind. Recommend (a) — keep fixture changes minimal until the corpus-build work lands, which will exercise all 6 source_types properly.\n- **Finding 2 (high)**: Rewrite D4. Since `vector_default` is fully derivable from canonical state (`_fathomdb_vector_rows` + canonical_nodes), use the existing `rebuild_shadow_state` / `RebuildKind` path: drop the old vec0 virtual table, recreate with the new schema, repopulate via the writer rebuild driver. Schema versioning belongs in `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` + `PRAGMA user_version`, not `operational_mutations`. The memo must cite the actual migration framework anchors.\n- **Finding 3 (medium)**: Remove or rewrite the secondary sign-pattern fixture in D6. The first fixture is sufficient on its own.\n\nFix-1 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-1.md`. Respawn implementer on the existing worktree `/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z`, existing branch.\n","numLines":51,"startLine":1,"totalLines":51}}}
