{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kuq3BBhZkvqg741BDy6fKJ","type":"tool_result","content":"125\t   note on the corpus card.\n126\t2. **Synthetic cross-doc chain generator: in 0.7.0 scope** —\n127\t   needed to test the vector implementation; bundles with\n128\t   Pack 2.\n129\t3. **Recall floor 0.90 @ k=10**: current bar; revisit after\n130\t   empirical run.\n131\t4. **CI artifact**: cache the corpus in GitHub Actions cache.\n132\t   License-clean sources (CNN/DailyMail Apache-2.0, OpenAlex\n133\t   CC0, Enron) can additionally be committed; CC-BY-NC-SA\n134\t   sources (ELITR) live in cache only, fetched at cache miss.\n135\t5. **Partition_key: `source_type`** — locked. Supersedes the\n136\t   `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff. Pack 1 schema MUST\n137\t   use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key.\n138\t\n139\tDefault corpus version for Pack 2 RED tests: **Version B\n140\t(~10K docs)** per the research recommendation. Sources:\n141\tEnron / EnronQA (emails), QMSum + ELITR (meetings), PMC OA +\n142\tS2ORC + OpenAlex (academic), CNN/DailyMail (news), Imperative\n143\tTo-Do (todos), public daily-log repos + synthetic generator\n144\t(notes).\n145\t\n146\tCorpus-build handoff:\n147\t`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-CORPUS-BUILD-HANDOFF.md`.\n148\t\n149\tThe PCACHE2 stack is still the right lock for AC-012 / AC-020;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15e9754f-2583-43b5-b988-10adeffaf9c5","uuid":"924812c1-41e5-4a1a-9e7b-45e7e52a51d3","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:36:16.302Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md","content":"   note on the corpus card.\n2. **Synthetic cross-doc chain generator: in 0.7.0 scope** —\n   needed to test the vector implementation; bundles with\n   Pack 2.\n3. **Recall floor 0.90 @ k=10**: current bar; revisit after\n   empirical run.\n4. **CI artifact**: cache the corpus in GitHub Actions cache.\n   License-clean sources (CNN/DailyMail Apache-2.0, OpenAlex\n   CC0, Enron) can additionally be committed; CC-BY-NC-SA\n   sources (ELITR) live in cache only, fetched at cache miss.\n5. **Partition_key: `source_type`** — locked. Supersedes the\n   `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff. Pack 1 schema MUST\n   use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key.\n\nDefault corpus version for Pack 2 RED tests: **Version B\n(~10K docs)** per the research recommendation. Sources:\nEnron / EnronQA (emails), QMSum + ELITR (meetings), PMC OA +\nS2ORC + OpenAlex (academic), CNN/DailyMail (news), Imperative\nTo-Do (todos), public daily-log repos + synthetic generator\n(notes).\n\nCorpus-build handoff:\n`dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-CORPUS-BUILD-HANDOFF.md`.\n\nThe PCACHE2 stack is still the right lock for AC-012 / AC-020;","numLines":25,"startLine":125,"totalLines":296}}}
