{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_011tFQrrHFUfaYTjxXCA5Ef2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TMJRhf5pznmh3CURFjgMXc","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md","old_string":"**Decision: extend the `source_type` vocabulary to include\n`\"doc\"` as the seventh allowed value, with the explicit\nsemantic \"synthetic / test fixture kind\".**\n\nMapping table (Pack 1, deterministic, total):\n\n| Incoming `kind` value | Resolved `source_type` |\n|-----------------------|------------------------|\n| `\"email\"`             | `email`                |\n| `\"article\"`           | `article`              |\n| `\"paper\"`             | `paper`                |\n| `\"meeting\"`           | `meeting`              |\n| `\"note\"`              | `note`                 |\n| `\"todo\"`              | `todo`                 |\n| `\"doc\"`               | `doc`                  |\n| anything else         | **error** — writer returns `EngineError::Storage` and refuses the insert (forces an explicit mapping-table extension at the next new kind). |\n\nRejected alternatives, with one-line reasoning:\n\n- (b) \"map `doc` to `article` by convention\" — would silently\n  conflate the synthetic fixture with the locked real-data\n  vocabulary; corrupts any future partition-key telemetry that\n  joins on `source_type`.\n- (c) \"leave `source_type` nullable for kinds without a mapping\" —\n  loses the partition_key benefit for the AC-013 fixture (the\n  fixture is exactly the row population a partition-key\n  pre-filter would have to cover) and breaks the \"partition_key\n  is locked\" guarantee in HITL Q5.\n- \"Keep `source_type` strictly to the 6-value vocab and skip\n  AC-013\" — the AC-013 fixture would either need a renamed kind\n  (changing every other test that reads it) or a parallel\n  bypass; both larger blast radii than admitting `doc` to the\n  vocabulary with an explicit \"test\" tag.\n\nCitation: HITL lock at\n`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135-137` (vocabulary +\n\"supersedes the `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff\"). The\n\"~6\" cardinality figure in the ADR § 2 / Pack 1 list is\ninformational, not a hard cap; extending to 7 by admitting the\nsynthetic `doc` value is consistent with the lock's intent\n(\"the source_type vocabulary is the authoritative set going\nforward\").\n\nThe mapping is implemented in a single Rust helper:\n\n```rust\nfn resolve_source_type(kind: &str) -> Result<&'static str, EngineError> {\n    Ok(match kind {\n        \"email\" => \"email\",\n        \"article\" => \"article\",\n        \"paper\" => \"paper\",\n        \"meeting\" => \"meeting\",\n        \"note\" => \"note\",\n        \"todo\" => \"todo\",\n        \"doc\" => \"doc\",\n        _ => return Err(EngineError::Storage),\n    })\n}\n```\n\n(no allocator pressure; returns `&'static str`; used at both\nwriter sites in D7.)","new_string":"**Decision: the locked 6-value `source_type` vocabulary holds\nunchanged. The synthetic test fixture kind `\"doc\"` is coerced\nat the writer to `source_type = \"article\"`; the vocabulary is\nnot extended.** No HITL re-open required — the lock at\n`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135-137` is honored\nexactly.\n\nMapping table (Pack 1, deterministic, total):\n\n| Incoming `kind` value | Resolved `source_type` |\n|-----------------------|------------------------|\n| `\"email\"`             | `email`                |\n| `\"article\"`           | `article`              |\n| `\"paper\"`             | `paper`                |\n| `\"meeting\"`           | `meeting`              |\n| `\"note\"`              | `note`                 |\n| `\"todo\"`              | `todo`                 |\n| `\"doc\"` (synthetic test fixture from `tests/perf_gates.rs:350`) | `article` (coerced) |\n| anything else         | **writer error** — fail the projection outcome (`EngineError::Storage`); do not silently default. |\n\nRationale for the `doc` -> `article` coercion: AC-013 seeds\nsynthetic doc-shaped bodies (long-form text) that are the most\nsemantically aligned with the `article` source within the locked\n6-value set. The coercion (a) preserves the partition_key\nutility for the AC-013 fixture rows (they aggregate under a real\nsource_type bucket the corpus-build work will also populate),\n(b) avoids any test churn — the fixture continues to write\n`kind=\"doc\"`; only the resolved `source_type` differs, (c)\nmatches what `CORPUS-1` (CNN/DailyMail acquisition, commit\n`27ab8df`) will land as the production article source. The\ncoercion is writer-internal; the canonical `kind` value is\npreserved verbatim in the `kind` metadata column (and in\n`_fathomdb_vector_rows`), so any consumer needing to distinguish\nfixture rows from corpus rows can still do so by reading `kind`.\n\nRejected alternatives:\n\n- \"Add `doc` as a 7th `source_type` value\" — extends the\n  HITL-locked vocabulary without authorization. This was the\n  original draft and is the blocking finding in the codex\n  verdict (`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-review-20260527T132959Z.md`\n  finding 1).\n- \"Rename the fixture kind from `doc` to one of the 6 locked\n  values\" — touches every test that reads the AC-013 fixture\n  (larger blast radius than a writer-side coercion).\n- \"Leave `source_type` nullable for unmapped kinds\" — loses the\n  partition_key benefit for the AC-013 fixture and breaks the\n  \"partition_key is locked\" guarantee in HITL Q5.\n\nCitation: HITL lock at\n`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135-137` (vocabulary +\n\"supersedes the `kind` default in the Pack 1 handoff\").\n\nThe mapping is implemented in a single Rust helper:\n\n```rust\nfn resolve_source_type(kind: &str) -> Result<&'static str, EngineError> {\n    Ok(match kind {\n        \"email\" => \"email\",\n        \"article\" => \"article\",\n        \"paper\" => \"paper\",\n        \"meeting\" => \"meeting\",\n        \"note\" => \"note\",\n        \"todo\" => \"todo\",\n        // Synthetic AC-013 test fixture; coerced to \"article\" so\n        // the 6-value HITL lock holds. See D3 rationale above.\n        \"doc\" => \"article\",\n        _ => return Err(EngineError::Storage),\n    })\n}\n```\n\n(no allocator pressure; returns `&'static str`; used at both\nwriter sites in D7.)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":447,"cache_read_input_tokens":44642,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":447},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15e9754f-2583-43b5-b988-10adeffaf9c5","uuid":"1337503c-1a96-42d4-8d54-ac3d08d9c273","request_id":"req_011CbTASN4bzxsKxefZqVu34"}
