{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01SBUfeTvR3xcELGQxHhvEXT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Unn2e6Rv68WGc5PdxYmS3g","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md","old_string":"## D4 — NOT NULL + migration strategy\n\nvec0 virtual tables do not support `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN`\n(sqlite-vec stores its columns in vec0-internal shadow tables;\nthe surface is `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE` or DROP+RECREATE). The\nmigration is therefore necessarily a table rebuild, not an in-\nplace ALTER.\n\n**Decision: land NOT NULL constraints from the start. The\nmigration is a single transactional rebuild — CREATE new vec0\nunder a staging name, INSERT...SELECT with `vec_quantize_binary`\non the fly, DROP old, RENAME — and the writer enforces\nnon-nullability from commit zero.**\n\nMigration shape (Pack 1, runs at `EngineRuntime::open` after the\nschema-version bump):\n\n```sql\nCREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default_v2 USING vec0(\n  embedding float[<dim>],\n  embedding_bin bit[<dim>],\n  source_type TEXT partition key,\n  kind TEXT,\n  created_at INTEGER\n);\n\nINSERT INTO vector_default_v2(\n  rowid, embedding, embedding_bin, source_type, kind, created_at\n)\nSELECT\n  v.rowid,\n  v.embedding,\n  vec_quantize_binary(v.embedding),\n  -- source_type / kind / created_at come from _fathomdb_vector_rows\n  -- joined on write_cursor = vector_default.rowid (see lib.rs:2174-2175\n  -- comment: vec0 rowid IS the canonical row's write_cursor).\n  resolve_source_type_sql(vr.kind),     -- registered SQL function (see below)\n  vr.kind,\n  unixepoch()                            -- best-effort backfill; no original timestamp survives\nFROM vector_default v\nJOIN _fathomdb_vector_rows vr ON vr.write_cursor = v.rowid;\n\nDROP TABLE vector_default;\nALTER TABLE vector_default_v2 RENAME TO vector_default;\n```\n\nThe migration runs inside a single writer transaction. Per the\nADR § 4 estimate it costs ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the 1 M-row\nfixture, ~64 s wall on the dev box — well under the existing\nworkflow timeout and the existing AC-013 seed cost (562 s on\ncanonical CI).\n\nNOT NULL enforcement:\n\n- `embedding`, `embedding_bin`, `source_type`, `kind`,\n  `created_at` are all written on every insert by Pack 1's\n  writer; no row can land with a NULL.\n- vec0 metadata columns do not have a declarative `NOT NULL`\n  constraint in the sqlite-vec syntax shown in\n  https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html.\n  Non-nullability is therefore enforced **at the writer**, not\n  by the DDL. This is a contract, not a column constraint.\n- The migration leaves no nullable row to clean up later, so\n  there is no Pack 2 \"tighten to NOT NULL\" follow-up.\n\n`resolve_source_type_sql` is a one-line SQLite scalar function\nregistered alongside `vec_quantize_binary` in\n`register_sqlite_vec_extension` (`lib.rs:3107`). It wraps the\nRust helper from D3. Falls back to a `CASE` expression inline if\nregistering a Rust function in that path is heavier than the\nmapping warrants — implementation chooses at code time, either\nshape is bit-for-bit equivalent for the 7-row mapping.\n\nA schema-version stamp lives in `operational_mutations`\n(existing collection used for excise audit rows at\n`lib.rs:2217-2221`); the migration is gated on\n`schema_version < 'vec0-pack1'` and writes the stamp on commit so\nre-opens are idempotent.","new_string":"## D4 — NOT NULL + migration strategy\n\nvec0 virtual tables in sqlite-vec `=0.1.7` (this repo's pin)\nsupport neither `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN` (a SQLite-level\nrule for virtual tables — https://www.sqlite.org/vtab.html) nor\n`ALTER TABLE ... RENAME` (rename support landed in sqlite-vec\n`v0.1.10-alpha.2`, April 2026, per the sqlite-vec release\nhistory). The migration is therefore a `DROP TABLE` + recreate\nunder the same name, with the row population rebuilt from\ncanonical state via the existing rebuild driver — not the\nstaging-table + RENAME shape originally drafted.\n\n**Decision: land NOT NULL constraints from the start. The\nmigration is a single writer-envelope rebuild — DROP the old\n`vector_default`, CREATE it again with the new schema under the\nsame name, then repopulate via the existing\n`Engine::rebuild_vec0` / `rebuild_shadow_state` path\n(`RebuildKind::Vec0`). The writer enforces non-nullability from\ncommit zero.**\n\nSchema versioning is owned by the engine's real migration\nframework: `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` at\n`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1238`, gated by\n`PRAGMA user_version` (probed at `lib.rs:2071-2072` for the\n`dump_schema` surface and at `lib.rs:2691` for the open-time\nsanity check). The new vec0 schema lands as a new\n`fathomdb_schema::Migration` step appended to the existing\nmigration array passed into `open_with_migrations`\n(`lib.rs:1119-1131`); `migrate_with_event_sink` bumps\n`PRAGMA user_version` on commit and gates re-entry on the same\nsentinel, so re-opens are naturally idempotent. The previously\nproposed `operational_mutations` schema stamp is **not** the\nschema-version owner — that collection is excise audit rows\n(`lib.rs:2217-2221`) — and is dropped from the design.\n\nMigration step (Pack 1):\n\n```sql\n-- Step body, executed by migrate_with_event_sink at lib.rs:1238.\n-- Runs inside the migration framework's transaction envelope.\nDROP TABLE vector_default;\nCREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default USING vec0(\n  embedding float[<dim>],\n  embedding_bin bit[<dim>],\n  source_type TEXT partition key,\n  kind TEXT,\n  created_at INTEGER\n);\n```\n\nRepopulation: deliberately not done by `INSERT ... SELECT` from\nthe old vec0 (the old table is dropped above and the new one\nhas zero rows). Instead, after the migration commits, the open\npath invokes the existing vec0 rebuild driver,\n`Engine::rebuild_vec0` (`lib.rs:1947`), which calls\n`run_rebuild` -> `rebuild_shadow_state` with `RebuildKind::Vec0`\n(`lib.rs:2234-2289`). That driver already knows how to:\n\n- Truncate the (newly-created, empty) `vector_default` and\n  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` shadow tables (no-op on first pass\n  but kept for the contract — see `lib.rs:2265-2270`).\n- Re-derive rows from `canonical_nodes` via the standard\n  projection pipeline, which writes through the Pack 1 writer\n  in D5 and therefore lands `embedding_bin`, `source_type`,\n  `kind`, `created_at` correctly on every row.\n\nThe whole sequence runs under the engine's existing\nsingle-writer envelope: `migrate_with_event_sink` holds the\nwriter for the DDL step, and `run_rebuild` re-acquires the\nwriter transaction (`lib.rs:2257-2259`) immediately after.\nThere is no window in which a reader can observe a partially\nrebuilt `vector_default`, because the engine does not advertise\nitself as open until `open_with_migrations` returns\n(`lib.rs:1238-1255`).\n\nNOT NULL enforcement:\n\n- `embedding`, `embedding_bin`, `source_type`, `kind`,\n  `created_at` are all written on every insert by Pack 1's\n  writer; no row can land with a NULL.\n- vec0 metadata columns do not have a declarative `NOT NULL`\n  constraint in the sqlite-vec DDL surface\n  (https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html).\n  Non-nullability is therefore enforced **at the writer**, not\n  by the DDL. This is a contract, not a column constraint.\n- The rebuild from canonical leaves no nullable row to clean up\n  later, so there is no Pack 2 \"tighten to NOT NULL\" follow-up.\n\nMigration cost: the rebuild scans `canonical_nodes` end-to-end\nand re-runs the projection writer for each row. The comparable\nbaseline is the AC-013 seed cost — 562 s on canonical CI per\n`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`\n— but the migration **does not** re-run the embedder (canonical\nstate already carries the f32 embeddings via the existing vec0\nrestore path used by the rebuild driver), so the wall time\nshould land well below 562 s on the 1 M-row fixture. The\n60-90 s ADR § 4 estimate remains the working budget; the seed\ntime is cited only as an upper bound. A concrete measurement\nlands in P1-IMPL's GREEN gate.\n\nIdempotence: `PRAGMA user_version` already guards re-entry. On\nthe second open the migration step is skipped by\n`migrate_with_event_sink`, the rebuild driver is not invoked,\nand `vector_default` keeps the rows from the first pass."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2541,"cache_read_input_tokens":45089,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2541},"output_tokens":58,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15e9754f-2583-43b5-b988-10adeffaf9c5","uuid":"f5c42103-a16a-4ade-b69b-52d1600dd16d","request_id":"req_011CbTAUdnUE2i27ifCMavmj"}
